|<!--drawing--> {{No}}
|<!--flow   --> {{No}}
|<!--parafmt--> {{Yes}}
|<!--links  --> {{Yes}}
|<!--images --> {{Yes}}<ref group="Notes">As the [[Rich Text Format|RTF]] format stores pictures internally as [[bitmap]]s (.bmp), this leads to large notebook files.</ref>
|<!--resize images --> {{Yes}}
|<!--tables --> {{Yes}}<ref group="Notes">Tables must be created in another program. After pasting the table into Keynote NF, one can edit the cells and add new rows, but changing the size of the columns and adding or removing columns is not possible. These operations can be done by pasting the table into another program (for example, MS Word).</ref>
