{{Infobox mountain | name = Domen | other_name = | photo = | photo_size = | photo_caption = | elevation_m = 164 | prominence_m = | range = | parent_peak = | location = [[Vardø]], [[Finnmark]], [[Norway]] | map = Finnmark#Norway | map_alt = Map of the location | map_caption = Location of the mountain | label = Domen | label_position = left | range_coordinates = | topo = | type = | age = | first_ascent = | easiest_route = | listing = | coordinates = {{coord|70|20|00|N|31|02|08|E|type:mountain_region:NO_scale:100000|format=dms|display=inline,title}} }}
'''Domen''' is a [[mountain]] on the [[Varanger Peninsula]] in eastern [[Finnmark]] county, [[Norway]]. The {{convert|164|m|adj=on}} tall mountain is located near the coast between the small [[fishing village]] [[Kiberg]] and the island of [[Vardøya]]. Domen is bare and flat-topped, with a steep slope towards the [[Barents Sea]] below. The [[European route E75]] highway which runs along the western side of the mountain from [[Svartnes]] to [[Kiberg]]. The road is often closed in the winter due to bad weather.<ref name="snl">{{cite web|url=http://snl.no/Domen|title=Domen|author=Store norske leksikon|authorlink=Store norske leksikon|language=Norwegian|accessdate=2013-03-01}}</ref>
==Name== The [[Old Norse]] name of the [[Arctic Sea]] was ''Dumbshaf''. This sea (''haf'') was named after the mountain ''Dumbr'' (an old form of ''Domen''). The name is probably related to the English word ''dumb'', but in what meaning is unclear.
==History and folklore== Domen is often associated with the [[witch trials]] in Finnmark during the 17th century. Vardø was the site of approximately 70 witch trials between 1601 and 1663. This was a large number, since there were only a couple of hundred inhabitants in the area at that time.
According to folklore, Vardø and Domen became infamous as ''the end of the world'', [[Ultima Thule]] and the entrance to [[Hell]] was said to be somewhere around Domen or Vardø, and so witches flew to Domen to meet the devil for [[Sabbath (witchcraft)|sabbath]].<ref>{{cite paper|last=Alm|first=Ellen Janette|title=Statens rolle i trolldomsprosessene i Danmark og Norge på 1500- og 1600-tallet|type=Thesis|publisher=University of Tromso|year=2000|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite paper|last=Willumsen|first=Liv Helene|title=Seventeenth-Century Witchcraft Trials in Scotland and Northern Norway|type=Thesis|publisher=University of Edinburgh|year=2008}}</ref>
==See also== *[[Blockula]] *[[Vardø witch trials]] *[[Vardø witch trials (1621)]]
