The '''''Encyclopedia of Recorded Sound''''' is a [[reference work]] which describes the [[history of sound recording]]s, from the time of [[Thomas Edison]] onwards.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.informaworld.com/smpp/title~db=all~content=t740991554 |title=Encyclopedia of Recorded Sound |publisher=Informaworld.com |access-date=2010-12-04}}</ref>{{dl|date=November 2015}}<ref>{{cite web |author-last=Pattanaik |author-first=Devdutt |url=http://www.flipkart.com/encyclopedia-recorded-sound-hoffman-frank-book-041593835x |title=Encyclopedia Of Recorded Sound. Frank  W. Hoffmann &#124; Flipkart Books |publisher=Flipkart.com |access-date=2010-12-04}}</ref>

