{{italic title}}
'''''Sangria: A Recipe for Love''''' is a 2009 [[novel]] written by [[Manuela Requena]] ({{ISBN|978-0979811678}}). It has been described as "the first ever book about cookery in Fiction form" and includes 25 recipes.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Sangria-A-Recipe-For-Love/dp/0979811678|title=Sangria; a recipe for love|publisher=Amazon|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref> The book won the Best Food Literature Book award for 2009 at the [[Gourmand World Cookbook Awards]] in [[Paris]], February 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://old.cookbookfair.com/winners.php?id=2009_c_32|title=Section 27: Literature|work=Gourmand Awards 2009: Cooking|accessdate=21 January 2013}}</ref>

